<div id="review_887811397" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/887811397" />
    <a title="Eddie Jones" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4632795-eddie-jones"><img alt="Eddie Jones" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1558010559p2/4632795.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/887811397?book_show_action=true">Mar 21, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eddie Jones" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eddie Jones" href="/user/show/4632795-eddie-jones">Eddie Jones</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Edie Melson</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Eddie by: </span>
      Eva Marie Everson
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer887811397" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2657907830526418447">Follows the classic romantic comedy formula based on deception. Somewhat predictable. As in, you know the couple will get together at the end. But the tag line about it being a Cinderella Love Story is accurate in the sense that the someone turns out to be a pumpkin (not saying whom). Has a little bit of a spiritual element but not so much that it turned me off. All in all, an easy read.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


